- Static Variables

+ declared by using keyword 'static'

+ static variables are not used very often
ex: when reading user input, using "Scanner" we will declare scanner as a
static variable

+ if changes are made to that variable, all other instances will see the effect
of the change.

- Instance Variables

+ they don't use the static keyword

+ Instance variables are also known as fields.

+ Instance variables belong to an instance of a class